thread.title: Obama raises $1.5 million at Seattle fundraiser
thread.title_full: Obama raises $1.5 million at Seattle fundraiser

author: The Associated Press
title: Obama raises $1.5 million at Seattle fundraiser
text:
Obama raises $1.5 million at Seattle fundraiser Barack Obama President Barack Obama waves as he boards Air Force One in Eugene Friday. Obama traveled to Roseburg to meet with families of the victims of the Oct. 1 shooting at Umpqua Community College. He then flew to fundraiser in Seattle to benefit Sen. Patty Murray, D-Wash. (Pablo Martinez Monsivais / AP) Comments 
SEATTLE (AP) â€” President Barack Obama's visit to Seattle this week was brief, but he succeeded in raising a lot of money for U.S. Patty Murray's re-election campaign. 
The Seattle Times estimates the a small reception with the president Friday raised more than $1 million. About 30 donors paid up to $33,400 per person to spend some quality time with the president before a bigger dinner. 
Then more than 1,400 people paid at least $250 for the dinner at the Westin hotel, which raised an estimated $500,000. 
The president flew to Seattle for the fundraisers after spending an hour in Roseburg Friday afternoon grieving with families affected by the mass fatal shooting at Umpqua Community College. 
Murray's 2016 re-election campaign had raised $6.7 million through June, as of the latest Federal Election Commission reports. 
-- The Associated Press
